===Etymology 3===

ほとけ (hotoke): ''hoto'' from {{etyl|zhx|ja|sort=ふつ'}} {{term|佛陀|tr=Fó​tuó|lang=cmn}}, itself from {{etyl|sa|ja|sort=ふつ'}} {{term|Buddha|lang=sa|sc=Latn}}; ''ke'' probably the suffix {{term|気|tr=ke|lang=ja}}, possibly added to signify [[mystical]] or [[visible]].

====Noun====
{{ja-noun|s|hira=ほとけ|rom=hotoke|kyu=佛}}

# A [[Buddha]]: an [[enlightened]] or [[awakened]] [[sentient]] being.
# A [[statue]] or [[image]] of any Buddha.
# The [[deceased]], a [[departed]] [[soul]].
# A term that a parent calls a child expressing parental affection: "my dear".
#* c. 890: [[w:Taketori Monogatari|Taketori Monogatari]] (page 7)
#*: 「我子の'''仏'''、変化の人と申ながら、こゝら大きさまでやしなひたてまつる心ざし、をろかならず。 [...]」
#* c. 890: [[w:Taketori Monogatari|Taketori Monogatari]] (page 61)
#*: 「あが'''仏'''、何事思ひたまふぞ。おぼすらんこと、何事ぞ」

====Proper noun====
{{ja-pos|s|proper|hira=ほとけ|rom=Hotoke|kyu=佛}}

# [[Śākyamuni]] [[Buddha]], Nepalese spiritual and philosophical teacher and founder of ''[[Buddhism]]''; Siddhartha Gautama.
# Any of the other Buddhas named in [[Buddhist]] [[scripture]]s.

